The Institution of democracy

-New Government

-   limited government: one that is restricted in its power and therefore will not infringe on the rights of its citizens
-   republic: a representative government in which an official represents the citizens of a society
-   popular sovereignty: a government that reflects the will of the people
-   democracy: a government in which its representatives and policies are decided uponby its people
-   consent of the governed

-   The people have the right to alter the government
